document_data.Description:
Moonbars were usually found in large crystals, typically 1 ft (30 cm) long by 4 in (10 cm) wide, which were rectangular with rounded corners. Milky white and opaque with a nacreous sheen, moonbars had a naturally smooth surface A typical specimen had a base value of 1,000gp.

Moonbars were considered sacred to [[Kiaransalee]] by her followers&mdash;appropriate for sacrifice, or to be consecrated for use, or recognized as boons or omens when found.{{Cite web enhancement/Deity Do's and Don'ts|12}}

Priestesses of [[Sehanine Moonbow]] wore [[holy symbol]]s carved from moonbar.
